On 3/31/06 4:03 PM, "Bart Dunn" <cb_dunn(-at-)yahoo.com> wrote:

> Does anyone know where you can get German ball joints for a baywindow?  OE
> VeeDub claims to have some, but they're actually Brazilian.  Thanks!

I haven't seen any German ball joints in a lately. There are two
manufacturers that I know of, ocap (Italy) and nakata (brazil). They are
both good. Probably not as good as one made by Febi, but we can't get Febi,
AFAIK. There are also Chinese ones available (stay away from those).


